Whereas the battles on the north bank of the River Raisin
			 were some of the largest engagements of the War of 1812, and the largest battle
			 ever to be fought on Michigan soil;

Whereas the River Raisin Battlefield Site was established
			 as a Michigan State Historic Site on February 18, 1956, and was placed on the
			 National Register of Historic Places on December 10, 1982;
